hopobject.body: Could you send me an application form? stafford pharmacy open sunday “The Scots could have won,” said Neil Wilson, who coordinates the cycling programme for the Glendale Development Trust, and who gets landed with cycling journalists, “But it rained all day and the burn below the ridge became a bog. The Scots pikemen broke formation and their cannon were siege cannon, so they fired right over the English instead of hitting them.” Then the English got stuck in with their ‘bills’, short, savage weapons converted from the humble agricultural billhook. Into this mess charged Stanley and his archers. Survivors trying to reach the Tweed had little chance and camp followers were caught in the slaughter.
